OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F439A1784029691
OL,3,CALN funding row throws Welsh
OL,4,CGovernment's budget plans into jeopardy
OL,6,FA row has erupted between Plaid Cymru
OL,7,Fand Welsh Labour over talks aimed at
OL,8,Freaching a deal over the Welsh
OL,9,FGovernment's spending plans.
OL,11,FPlaid Cymru has accused Labour of
OL,12,F"walking away" from an offer of #80m
OL,13,Ffunding for Additional Learning Needs
OL,14,F(ALN) in schools.
OL,16,FLabour rejects both claims, saying
OL,17,Fthat it's offered continued talks and
OL,18,Fthat #80m over two years is not
OL,19,Fenough. It's holding out for #100m
OL,20,Fspending in this financial year.
OL,26,@tD@AOUtD@NO]
