PN,43904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F439A1784029691
OL,3,CALN funding row throws Welsh
OL,4,CGovernment's budget plans into jeopardy
OL,6,FThe main opposition party, Reform UK
OL,7,FWales, has said that it won't back the
OL,8,Fsupplementary budget when it comes to
OL,9,Fthe Senedd next Tuesday (14 July).
OL,10,FWelsh Conservatives have also ruled
OL,11,Fout supporting it.
OL,13,FThat leaves Labour as the only option
OL,14,Ffor a deal and talks haven't gone
OL,15,Fsmoothly.
OL,17,FThe group, led by its interim leader
OL,18,FKen Skates, has made extra funding for
OL,19,FALN the focus of discussions.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/13
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
